menu "WiFi Station"

    config WIFI_STA_MAX_RETRY
        int "Maximum connection retry attempts before giving up"
        default 10
        range 1 50
        help
            Number of times the WiFi station will attempt to reconnect
            after a disconnection event before logging a fatal error
            and rebooting. Each retry waits WIFI_STA_RETRY_DELAY_MS
            milliseconds before the next attempt.

    config WIFI_STA_RETRY_DELAY_MS
        int "Delay between retry attempts (ms)"
        default 3000
        range 500 30000
        help
            Milliseconds to wait between consecutive reconnect attempts.
            3000 ms (3 seconds) is a reasonable default. Increase this
            on congested networks where rapid retries worsen the problem.

    config WIFI_STA_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_MS
        int "Initial connection timeout (ms) [OBSOLETE — not used]"
        default 15000
        range 5000 60000
        help
            Formerly the maximum time to wait for the first connection.
            No longer consulted: wifi_sta_connect() now blocks indefinitely
            (portMAX_DELAY) and relies on the absolute timeout below to
            force a portal fallback on permanent failures.

    config WIFI_STA_ABSOLUTE_TIMEOUT_MINUTES
        int "Absolute disconnection ceiling before portal fallback (minutes)"
        default 20
        range 1 120
        help
            Absolute time ceiling in minutes before a continuously
            disconnected device erases credentials and restarts into
            the provisioning portal. This guards against permanent
            NO_AP_FOUND loops caused by an SSID typo during provisioning.
            The timer starts on the first disconnect after boot and resets
            to zero each time a valid IP address is obtained.

endmenu
